    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term referring to members of several invertebrate phyla of various disparate groups, including the entire phylum of annelids. They have in common soft, elongated bodies lacking a hard outer covering.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
